WHAT THIS FORM IS SUPPOSED TO DO:
==============================================
 
This is the CarePath Medical patient registration form for homework 3.
It builds on homework 2 by moving all validation from HTML pattern
attributes into JavaScript functions that run onthefly as the user
types or leaves each field.
 
The Submit button is hidden when the page loads and only appears
after the user clicks Validate and all fields pass. Error messages
appear next to each field immediately as the user enters bad data,
and disappear as soon as the user corrects the mistake.
 
==============================================
WHAT I AM HAPPY WITH THAT IS WORKING:
==============================================
 
1. The Submit button stays hidden until all fields pass validation.
   It only appears after the Validate button is clicked and no
   errors are found.
 
2. Error messages appear and disappear on the fly as the user
   types in each field, without waiting for a submit click.
 
3. The SSN field auto formats itself as the user types, inserting
   dashes after the 3rd and 5th digits automatically.
 
4. The User ID is automatically converted to lowercase and the
   field is updated to show the lowercase version.
 
5. The email field is forced to lowercase as the user types.
 
6. The date of birth field uses JavaScript to set min and max
   limits dynamically based on today's date, so no hard-coded
   dates are used.
 
7. The password field checks for uppercase, lowercase, and a
   number requirement, and also checks that the password does
   not equal the user ID.
 
8. The two password fields are compared in real time as the
   user types in the second field.
 
==============================================
WHAT I DID NOT YET GET WORKING:
==============================================
 
1. The error count tracker can sometimes get out of sync if
   the user clicks Validate multiple times. A full reset of
   the counter is done each time Validate is clicked to
   work around this. I did not know what else to do. 
 
2. The form does not yet check whether the password contains
   part of the user's first or last name.
 
3. Address line 2 validation only runs on blur, not oninput,
   since it is optional and would show errors while the user
   is still typing.
 
